ra, Tuscany, Italy":"Mulazzo, Massa-Carrara, Tuscany, Italy","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Malaspina","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Tino, Aldo, Antonio, Carmella, Guido, Mario.","Italian:","from <i>mala</i> (feminine of <i>malo</i>) ‘bad, evil’ + <i>spina</i> ‘thorn’, applied as a nickname and personal name."],"variants":[{"name":"La Spina","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Sal, Angelo, Mario, Rosario, Sebastiano, Carmelo, Gino, Giuseppe, Ignazio, Javier, Orazio, Salvatore.","Italian (southern):","from <i>spina</i> ‘thorn’ (from Latin <i>spina</i>), with the definite article <i>la</i>, applied as a topographic name for someone who lived by a thorn bush or in an area of scrubland, or (in a transferred sense) for someone who lived by the crest or ridge of a hill. It could also be a nickname for a tall, thin, spiky person."]},{"name":"Spina","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Ciro, Antonio, Carmine, Angelo, Rocco, Vito, Carlo, Carmela, Santo, Vincenza, Vincenzo.","Italian:","from <i>spina</i> ‘thorn, thorn bush’, used as a nickname in various senses, including ‘distress, sorrow’ (alluding to Christ's crown of thorns), and also as a personal name; or alternatively a habitational name from any of numerous places called with this word (in some instances with reference to the dedication of a shrine)."]}]},{"name":"Argenta","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Pio.","Italian: variant of   Argento  .","Italian: habitational name from Argenta in Emilia-Romagna."],"variants":[{"name":"Argento","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Angelo, Sal, Antonio, Calogero, Giuseppe, Carmella, Claudio, Dino, Filippo, Mario, Natale, Paolo, Pasquale, Renato, Rocco.","Italian:","from <i>argento</i> ‘silver’, perhaps sometimes applied as a nickname for someone with silvery gray hair, but more often a metonymic occupational name for a silversmith."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Argenta Malaspina was born about 1191, in Italy as the daughter of Signore Corrado Malaspina. She married Antonio Grimaldi Spinola in Italy. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1191–":"umbes 1191–Surnud","1191–Female":"1191–Surnud","1187–Male":"1187–Surnud","1219–Male":"1219–Surnud","1230–1281":"1230–1281","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","about 1191":"umbes 1191","aproximadamente 1219":"umbes 1219","1187":"1187","1230":"1230","1160":"1160","1281":"1281","1219":"1219","1191":"1191","Itália":"Itaalia","Mulazzo, Massa-Carrara, Tuscany, Italy":"Mulazzo, Massa-Carrara, Toscana, Itaalia"},"fi":{"about 1191–":"noin 1191–Kuollut","1191–Female":"1191–Kuollut","1187–Male":"1187–Kuollut","1219–Male":"1219–Kuollut","1230–1281":"1230–1281","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","about 1191":"noin 1191","aproximadamente 1219":"noin 1219","1187":"1187","1230":"1230","1160":"1160","1281":"1281","1219":"1219","1191":"1191","Itália":"Italia","Mulazzo, Massa-Carrara, Tuscany, Italy":"Mulazzo, Massa-Carrara, Toscana, Italia"},"fr":{"about 1191–":"environ 1191–Décédée","1191–Female":"1191–Décédée","1187–Male":"1187–Décédé","1219–Male":"1219–Décédé","1230–1281":"1230–1281","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","about 1191":"environ 1191","aproximadamente 1219":"environ 1219","1187":"1187","1230":"1230","1160":"1160","1281":"1281","1219":"1219","1191":"1191","Itália":"Italie","Mulazzo, Massa-Carrara, Tuscany, Italy":"Mulazzo, Massa-Carrara, Toscana, Italie","lifeSummary":"Argenta Malaspina est née environ 1191, à Italie, fille de Signore Corrado Malaspina. Elle a épousé Antonio Grimaldi Spinola à Italie. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1191–":"um 1191–Verstorben","1191–Female":"1191–Verstorben","1187–Male":"1187–Verstorben","1219–Male":"1219–Verstorben","1230–1281":"1230–1281","1160–Male":"1160–V